      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 15: The build image installs Rust by piping a live network script into `sh` and uses the moving `stable` toolchain. This makes package builds non-reproducible and adds supply-chain risk. Prefer distro packages or pin the rustup-init binary/toolchain with checksum verification. Example:\n```suggestion\nARG RUST_TOOLCHAIN\u003d1.86.0\n# Install rustc/cargo from a pinned, verified source or distro package, then:\nRUN rustup toolchain install ${RUST_TOOLCHAIN} --profile minimal \u0026\u0026 \\\n    rustup default ${RUST_TOOLCHAIN}\n```",
      "revId": "e537aba248f05f13aabe3aa8059b90a64dca990e",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
