      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 19: 🔴 Critical Issues - Must fix before merge: `chmod -R a+rwX /usr/local/rustup /usr/local/cargo` makes the Rust toolchain and cargo binaries world-writable. Any unprivileged process in the image can replace `cargo`/`rustc` and execute arbitrary code during package builds. The build user only needs read/execute access, not write access. Use root-owned, non-world-writable permissions, or chown only the cache directories that genuinely need writes.\n```suggestion\nRUN curl --proto \u0027\u003dhttps\u0027 --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs \\\n        | sh -s -- -y --profile minimal --default-toolchain stable \u0026\u0026 \\\n    chmod -R a+rX /usr/local/rustup /usr/local/cargo\n```",
      "revId": "e537aba248f05f13aabe3aa8059b90a64dca990e",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
