      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 107: The `link` attribute accepts and persists arbitrary href values. If these anchors are later opened by Qt or copied/rendered elsewhere, `file:`, `javascript:`, or other non-web schemes can become a local file exposure or script/handler launch vector. Validate links before applying them and only allow expected schemes such as http/https. Example:\n```suggestion\n} else if (key \u003d\u003d QLatin1String(\"link\")) {\n    const QUrl url(v.toString());\n    const bool safeLink \u003d url.isValid() \u0026\u0026 (url.scheme() \u003d\u003d QLatin1String(\"http\") || url.scheme() \u003d\u003d QLatin1String(\"https\"));\n    if (on \u0026\u0026 safeLink) {\n        f.setAnchor(true);\n        f.setAnchorHref(url.toString());\n        f.setForeground(LINK_COLOR);\n        f.setFontUnderline(true);\n    } else {\n        f.setAnchor(false);\n        f.setAnchorHref(QString());\n        f.clearForeground();\n        f.setFontUnderline(false);\n    }\n}\n```",
      "revId": "e537aba248f05f13aabe3aa8059b90a64dca990e",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
