      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Medium] Line 263: 🟡 Suggestions - Improvements to consider: malformed or hostile remote delta JSON is silently accepted and partially clamped. Negative `retain` values can move `index` backwards, very large operations are clamped without rejecting the edit, and invalid JSON simply returns without surfacing the sync problem. Since this data comes from peers through the daemon, validate the delta shape and bounds before mutating the QTextDocument, and log/reject invalid operations instead of applying a best-effort partial edit.\n```suggestion\nconst auto parseError \u003d QJsonParseError{};\nconst QJsonDocument jd \u003d QJsonDocument::fromJson(deltaJson.toUtf8(), \u0026parseError);\nif (parseError.error !\u003d QJsonParseError::NoError || !jd.isArray()) {\n    qWarning() \u003c\u003c \"Invalid collaborative rich-text delta\" \u003c\u003c parseError.errorString();\n    return;\n}\n// Before applying each op, reject negative retain/delete values and ranges past docLen.\n```",
