      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 267: Remote deltas are applied with `qBound()` on retain/delete ranges, which silently truncates invalid CRDT operations. That can make the local rich document diverge from peers instead of rejecting or surfacing a corrupt/out-of-order delta. Validate every operation against the current document length and abort/log when an operation is out of range. Example:\n```suggestion\nconst int docLen \u003d d-\u003echaracterCount() - 1;\nif (index \u003c 0 || n \u003c 0 || index + n \u003e docLen) {\n    qWarning() \u003c\u003c \"Invalid collaborative rich-text delta\" \u003c\u003c deltaJson;\n    applyingRemote_ \u003d false;\n    return;\n}\ncc.setPosition(index);\ncc.setPosition(index + n, QTextCursor::KeepAnchor);\n```",
      "revId": "e537aba248f05f13aabe3aa8059b90a64dca990e",
